name: bombay-hook-national-wildlife-refuge-quarterly-narrative-report-february-march-and-april-1-b7dd9
notes: This narrative report for Bombay Hook NWR outlines Refuge accomplishments from February through April of 1942. The report begins by summarizing the weather conditions and water conditions during this period. Wildlife- including migratory birds, upland game birds, furbearers, predators, rodents, mammals, and raptors- is also covered. The Refuge development and maintenance section discusses physical developments and farming. The public relations section of the report describes Refuge visitors.
